Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Flowable Developer* role with *Artech Information Systems*. I bring over three years of professional experience building Java and Spring Boot backend services, designing REST API integrations, and orchestrating complex end-to-end process workflows — along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the depth of REST API integration and process orchestration this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed an end-to-end process workflow platform using Temporal — decomposing multi-step operations into service tasks with exception handling, retry policies, and resume-on-failure semantics that orchestrated flows across distributed REST API backends; this maps closely to the delegate, listener, and custom-task patterns central to Flowable BPM development. Alongside it, I built a FastMCP-based REST API integration layer exposing 160+ backend actions consumed by agents across multi-tenant workflows, with JSON schema validation, Pydantic contracts, and OpenTelemetry instrumentation for production observability — exactly the kind of API-first integration design this role requires for connecting policy admin, underwriting, and document systems. I also built a visual workflow platform with React Flow and TypeScript backed by Temporal for durable, resumable orchestration with live Redis progress tracking, and GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines with trace-based evals to gate every deployment. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a REST API-driven, cloud-agnostic Storage Service in Java and Spring Boot with PostgreSQL and Redis — giving me direct hands-on experience with the Java/Spring Boot stack this role relies on daily. I also orchestrated long-running business processes with AWS Step Functions using exception-handling and retry policies across 100K+ weekly executions, and optimized PostgreSQL relational database performance with window functions and materialized views to support scalable data access. Together, these roles have equipped me to build Flowable services, integrate REST APIs across insurance systems, and own end-to-end process reliability from development through production support.

I have always been passionate about empowering businesses through applied human intelligence and connecting people with the right technology solutions — values that sit at the heart of Artech's mission. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

